      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's true that being a source of concern for your children can add to their stress levels, but try not to equate your well-being with their ability to move forward. A clean break may bring a temporary sense of relief to your children, but could also mean abandoning someone who needs them now in ways that go beyond just emotional support. Consider finding ways to support them in their busy lives, like helping with small tasks or running errands together, rather than simply stepping aside.",
